Piramal Drops Plan to Sell His Stake in Property Fund, ET Says

-- B y   A m e y a   K a r v e
-- 
2011-04-29T03:18:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/piramal-drops-plan-to-sell-his-stake-in-property-fund-et-says.html
Ajay Piramal, chairman of  Piramal
Healthcare Ltd. (PIHC) , has dropped plans to sell his 85 percent stake
in property fund Indiareit Fund Advisors Pvt. as he plans to
invest the corpus in his real-estate business, the Economic
Times reported, citing at least three people familiar with the
development, which it didnâ€™t identify.  Piramal was in talks with Religare Enterprises Ltd., a
financial services company backed by billionaire brothers
Malvinder and Shivinder Singh, to sell his stake for more than 3
billion rupees, the report said. The transaction was to close by
